1 SUMMARY
1
22 This bill changes the name of the Land Application Contaminant Monitoring Fund to
33 the Well Contamination Response Fund and changes the activities for which funding may
44 be used. It provides funding for private drinking water wells impacted by hazardous
55 substances, including perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl substances. Funding may be used
66 for testing, remediation, the installation and maintenance of filter treatment systems,
77 connection to local water district networks and the provision of bottled drinking water. The
88 bill also directs the Department of Environmental Protection to determine eligibility
99 requirements for the funding through rulemaking.
